  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN134.1-kilavi">viṉaimuṟṟi maṟuttarā <app><lem>niṉṟa</lem><rdg wit="#C2 #C3 #C9v #RK">mīṇṭa</rdg></app> talaimakaṉ <app><lem>pākaṟkuc</lem><rdg wit="#C2 #C3 #C9v">ṟērpākaṟkuc</rdg></app> colliyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What HE, who was arguing after having completed the work, said to the charioteer.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN134.1">
                <l>vāṉam vāyppak kaviṉik kāṉaṅ</l>
                <l>kamañcūṉ māmaḻaik kārpayan tiṟutteṉa</l>
                <l>maṇimaruḷ pūvai yaṇimala riṭaiyiṭaic</l>
                <l>cempuṟa mūtāy parattali ṉaṉpaṉ</l>
                <l>mullai vīkaḻa ṟāya valalōṉ</l>
                <l>ceykai yaṉṉa cennilap puṟaviṉ</l>
                <l>vā<supplied>a</supplied>p pāṇi vayaṅkutoḻiṟ kalimāt</l>
                <l>tā<supplied>a</supplied>t tōḷiṇai mella votuṅka</l>
                <l><supplied>vi</supplied>ṭimaṟan tēmati valava kuvimukai</l>
                <l>vāḻai vāṉpū vūḻuṟu <supplied>puti</supplied>rnta</l>
                <l>voḻikulai yaṉṉa tirimarup pēṟṟoṭu</l>
                <l>ka<supplied>ṇai</supplied>kkā lampiṇai kāmar puṇarnilai</l>
                <l>kaṭumāṉ ṟēroli kēṭpi</l>
                <l>ṉaṭunāṭ kūṭṭa mākalu muṇṭē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>In the woodlands with soil red like the work</l>
                <l>of an expert, when jasmine blossoms become loose [and] spread, (5f.)</l>
                <l>a good many, because of the spreading of cochineals with red backs</l>
                <l>right among the decorative blossoms of the sapphire-like bilberry,</l>
                <l>since fully pregnant dark clouds tarried over the forest,</l>
                <l>as the rainy season produced [them], being beautiful as they gather in the sky, (1-4)</l>
                <l>forget the thunder [and] go, charioteer, (9a-c)</l>
                <l>while the pair with galloping shoulders tread softly,</l>
                <l>the spirited horses whose glowing task is a leaping rhythm. (7f.)</l>
                <l>When the round-legged pretty doe, in a desirable state of union</l>
                <l>with [her] stag with horns twisted like the bunches that remain</l>
                <l>when, at [their] turn, the pure flowers of the plantain with piling buds dropped off,</l>
                <l>hears the sound of the chariot with fast horses, (9d-13)</l>
                <l>[our] midnight meeting is to take place, too. (14)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
